{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0448dfa0-a289-48d9-b310-3af8bdb072ea","content":"I don't see a `.dmp` file in the current directory. Here's what I can tell you:\n\n**This environment has limited dump analysis tools** — `dotnet-dump` (the primary CLI analyzer) is not installed, and neither is `lldb` or `windbg`.\n\n### How to analyze your dump\n\n**Option 1 — Install `dotnet-dump` here and upload your file:**\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\ndotnet-dump analyze <your-file>.dmp\n```\nI can install it and walk you through the analysis if you upload or provide the path to your `.dmp` file.\n\n**Option 2 — Analyze locally on your machine** (recommended for large dumps):\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\ndotnet-dump analyze crash.dmp\n```\nKey commands inside the analyzer:\n| Command | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `clrstack` | Managed call stack of crashing thread |\n| `pe` | Print last exception |\n| `threads` | List all managed threads |\n| `dumpheap -stat` | Heap summary (for OOM) |\n| `syncblk` | Deadlock investigation |\n\n**Option 3 — Use Visual Studio** (Windows): Open the `.dmp` directly → \"Debug with Managed Only.\"\n\nWould you like me to install `dotnet-dump` here so we can analyze the file together? If so, please share the dump file path or upload it.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"dc19447f-ec67-49de-ada3-4b0fb17da784","outputTokens":346,"requestId":"D809:E621D:343BFFD:394D89D:69FBF1B8"},"id":"6640126e-3232-4bc6-90b1-d782b9f11007","timestamp":"2026-05-07T01:58:26.267Z","parentId":"26dacfc6-6dd6-4d6e-8bc3-bad2774441e6"}
